3. Common Cash Management Challenges In Canada

Canada is a mature market. As such, one need not face a shortage of cash in its financial systems. Canadian society’s maturing beliefs when it comes to using electronic money brings in the need for proper protection over cash availability. The current Canadian landscape still sees more consumer adoption of cash and plastic. This has led to a common cash management challenge of:

Controlling distribution of cash at point-of-sale. With Canada’s population heavily engaged in distributing and using physical cash, much of the industry in Canada has to come up with a way to account for the same. This entails the threat of:
